y** for tomorrow? (If you only accomplish one thing, what should it be?)\nSystem (untrusted): \nSystem (untrusted): **🙏 Gratitude:**\nSystem (untrusted): Name one person, one object, or one experience you are genuinely grateful for tonight.\nSystem (untrusted): \nSystem (untrusted): ***\nSystem (untrusted): \nSystem (untrusted): **A Note on Implementation:**\nSystem (untrusted): \nSystem (untrusted): To make this most effective, I recommend taking time to write down brief answers for these sections. If you'd like me to prompt you for specific areas—for example, focusing only on career, family, or personal development—please let me know!\nSystem (untrusted): \nSystem (untrusted): *Sending you peace for the evening ahead.*\n\nRead HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/dai/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Wednesday, April 29th, 2026 - 10:26 PM (America/Los_Angeles) / 2026-04-30 05:26 UTC","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"a77532f1","parentId":"ff26e648","timestamp":"2026-04-30T05:26:35.276Z"}
