{"type":"message","id":"7bbec3f8","parentId":"4c504b03","timestamp":"2026-04-30T08:28:39.013Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-20 17:28:33 PDT] GOOD MORNING\nSystem: \nSystem: BIBLE: \"Let the favor of the Lord our God be upon us, and establish the work of our hands\" (Psalm 90:17). Apply this by working with excellence today, trusting that the results are in His hands.\nSystem: \nSystem: WEATHER: Cool and crisp. High of 61°F. Wind advisory in effect—be mindful of gear and outdoor activities.\nSystem: \nSystem: TODAY'S PRIORITY: Execute the highest-leverage task first. No distractions until the primary objective is complete.\nSystem: \nSystem: FAMILY FOCUS: Undivided attention. Put the phone away and engage in a 15-minute one-on-one conversation with each child.\nSystem: \nSystem: COACHING FOCUS: Standards over feelings. Enforce the small details of discipline; if you overlook the small things, the big things will fail.\nSystem: \nSystem: STOIC PRINCIPLE: Dichotomy of Control. Focus exclusively on your own effort and reactions; ignore the noise and variables you cannot change.\nSystem: \nSystem: PERSONAL DISCIPLINE: Zero compromise on the morning routine. Wake up, execute, and lead.\nSystem: \nSystem: TONIGHT'S QUESTION: Where did I choose comfort over growth today, and how will I correct it tomorrow?\n\nRead HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/dai/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Monday, April 20th, 2026 - 5:56 PM (America/Los_Angeles) / 2026-04-21 00:56 UTC"}],"timestamp":1776732993893}}
